-- Amadeus Shares Fall as Much as 6.9% After IAG Hedge
-- B y   B e n   S i l l s
-- 2012-08-08T10:54:43Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-08-08/amadeus-shares-fall-as-much-as-6-9-after-iag-hedge-correct-.html
(Corrects to show Nomura sole counterparty in fourth
paragraph.)  Amadeus IT Holding SA (AMS)  fell as much as
6.9 percent in Madrid trading after  International Consolidated
Airlines Group SA (IAG)  hedged a 6.7 percent stake in the company.  Amadeus fell as low as 16.23 euros and traded down 4.9
percent at 16.58 euros at 10:23 a.m.  IAG hedged its stake at 16.50 euros per share it said in a
regulatory filing today.  Nomura Holdings Inc., the sole counterparty in the
derivatives transaction, sold 492 million euros ($609 million)
in Amadeus shares today to hedge its position in the deal.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ben Sills in Madrid at 
